<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">

  <!-- Header -->
  <div class="mb-8">
    <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Publish Your OOS</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm">Paste your CLAUDE.md (or any file that describes how your AI agents work together). We handle the rest.</p>
  </div>

  <form id="publish-form">

    <!-- MAIN INPUT: Paste area (always visible, front and center) -->
    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border mb-4">
      <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-3">
        <label for="oos-content" class="font-semibold text-sm text-gray-700">Your OOS Content</label>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <button type="button" onclick="loadExample()" class="text-xs px-3 py-1.5 bg-otp-50 text-otp-600 rounded-lg hover:bg-otp-100 font-medium transition-colors">Load Example</button>
          <label class="text-xs px-3 py-1.5 bg-gray-50 text-gray-600 rounded-lg hover:bg-gray-100 font-medium transition-colors cursor-pointer">
            Upload File
            <input type="file" id="file-input" accept=".md,.markdown,.txt" class="hidden">
          </label>
        </div>
      </div>

      <textarea id="oos-content" name="rawContent" rows="24"
        class="w-full font-mono text-sm border rounded-lg p-4 focus:border-otp-500 focus:ring-1 focus:ring-otp-500 resize-y"
        placeholder="Paste your CLAUDE.md content here.

This is the file that describes how your AI agents coordinate -- their roles, rules, tools, escalation patterns, and what you learned the hard way.

Don't have one yet? Click 'Load Example' above to see what an OOS looks like, or use the prompt generator below to create one with any AI."></textarea>

      <div class="flex justify-between mt-2 text-xs text-gray-400">
        <span id="word-count">0 words</span>
        <span id="claim-count">0 claims detected</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- HELPER: Don't have a CLAUDE.md? -->
    <details class="mb-4 bg-otp-50 border border-otp-200 rounded-lg">
      <summary class="px-5 py-3 cursor-pointer font-medium text-sm text-otp-700 flex items-center justify-between">
        Don't have a CLAUDE.md yet? Generate one with AI.
        <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-otp-400 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
      </summary>
      <div class="px-5 pb-5">
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-3">Copy this prompt, paste it into Claude, ChatGPT, or any AI. Replace the bracketed sections with your details. Then paste the output above.</p>
        <div class="relative">
          <pre id="generation-prompt" class="bg-gray-900 text-gray-100 text-xs p-4 rounded-lg overflow-x-auto max-h-64 overflow-y-auto whitespace-pre-wrap leading-relaxed">I need you to generate an OOS (Organizational Operating System) file for my organization.

Here is what we do: [Describe your business in 2-3 sentences]

Here is our AI setup:
[List your AI agents, automations, or AI-augmented workflows. For each one, describe:
- What it does
- What tools it uses
- What it owns vs. what it does NOT own
- Who/what it reports to or escalates to]

Here are the rules we follow:
[List any rules, policies, or patterns you have about how your AI operates.
Examples: "All emails require human approval before sending",
"The analytics bot reports but never recommends",
"If two agents disagree, the founder decides within 24 hours"]

Here are things that went wrong:
[List 2-5 failures, mistakes, or surprises you discovered while building
your AI setup. Be specific. These are often the most valuable claims.]

Here are the boundaries between AI and human:
[What decisions are human-only? What does AI handle autonomously?
Where is the line?]

Now generate an OOS file in this exact format:

1. YAML frontmatter between --- delimiters with: oos_version "1.0",
   org_pseudonym, industry, org_size (solo/small/medium/large/enterprise),
   template (agent_army/value_chain/org_chart), agent_count, platforms
   used, generated_at (ISO timestamp), version 1, parent_version null,
   word_count, claim_count, confidence_distribution (high/medium/low
   counts), evidence_distribution (counts per evidence type)

2. A Purpose section (2-3 sentences)

3. A Prime Directives section (3-5 top-level rules)

4. At minimum 15 claims using this format:

**[C001]** section_name
- **Rule:** [Clear, specific rule]
- **Why:** [Why this exists]
- **Failure mode:** [What breaks when violated]
- **Confidence:** HIGH | MEDIUM | LOW
- **Evidence:** HUMAN_DEFINED_RULE | OBSERVED_ONCE | OBSERVED_REPEATEDLY
  | MEASURED_RESULT | INFERENCE | SPECULATION
- **Scope:** [Where this applies]

Sections: core_operating_rules, agent_roles_and_authority,
coordination_patterns, operational_heuristics, failure_patterns,
human_ai_boundary_conditions

Rules for claims:
- Every claim must have all 6 fields
- Be specific and concrete, not generic
- Failure modes should describe real consequences
- Include at least 2-3 failure_patterns claims
- Total word count between 1800-3000 words
- Minimum 10 claims, aim for 15-25</pre>
          <button type="button" onclick="copyPrompt()" id="copy-prompt-btn"
            class="absolute top-2 right-2 px-3 py-1.5 bg-otp-500 text-white rounded text-xs font-medium hover:bg-otp-400">
            Copy Prompt
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </details>

    <!-- OPTIONAL: Template selector (collapsed, auto-detected) -->
    <details class="mb-6">
      <summary class="text-xs text-gray-400 cursor-pointer hover:text-gray-600">Advanced: Change template type (auto-detected from your content)</summary>
      <div class="mt-3 grid grid-cols-3 gap-3">
        <label class="border rounded-lg p-3 cursor-pointer hover:border-otp-500 has-[:checked]:border-otp-500 has-[:checked]:bg-otp-50 text-center">
          <input type="radio" name="template" value="agent_army" class="sr-only" checked>
          <div class="font-medium text-xs">Agent Army</div>
          <div class="text-[10px] text-gray-400 mt-0.5">Named agents with roles</div>
        </label>
        <label class="border rounded-lg p-3 cursor-pointer hover:border-otp-500 has-[:checked]:border-otp-500 has-[:checked]:bg-otp-50 text-center">
          <input type="radio" name="template" value="value_chain" class="sr-only">
          <div class="font-medium text-xs">Value Chain</div>
          <div class="text-[10px] text-gray-400 mt-0.5">Process flow</div>
        </label>
        <label class="border rounded-lg p-3 cursor-pointer hover:border-otp-500 has-[:checked]:border-otp-500 has-[:checked]:bg-otp-50 text-center">
          <input type="radio" name="template" value="org_chart" class="sr-only">
          <div class="font-medium text-xs">Org Chart</div>
          <div class="text-[10px] text-gray-400 mt-0.5">Department mapping</div>
        </label>
      </div>
    </details>

    <!-- PUBLISH BUTTON -->
    <button type="button" onclick="publishOOS()" id="publish-btn"
      class="w-full px-6 py-4 bg-otp-500 text-white rounded-xl font-semibold text-base hover:bg-otp-400 transition-colors disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-not-allowed">
      Publish to OTP
    </button>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 text-center mt-2">We auto-fix formatting issues, scan for PII, extract claims, and score quality. You can always unpublish later.</p>

    <!-- Results -->
    <div id="validation-results" class="mt-6 hidden">
      <div id="fix-results" class="hidden mb-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-green-700 mb-2" id="fix-header"></h3>
        <div id="fix-list" class="space-y-1"></div>
      </div>
      <div id="unfixable-results" class="hidden mb-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-orange-600 mb-2" id="unfixable-header"></h3>
        <div id="unfixable-list" class="space-y-2"></div>
      </div>
      <div id="validation-errors" class="hidden">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-red-600 mb-2">Issues to fix before publishing</h3>
        <div id="error-list" class="space-y-2"></div>
      </div>
      <div id="validation-warnings" class="hidden mt-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-yellow-600 mb-2">Suggestions</h3>
        <div id="warning-list" class="space-y-2"></div>
      </div>
      <div id="pii-flags" class="hidden mt-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-red-600 mb-2">Personal Information Detected</h3>
        <div id="pii-list" class="space-y-2"></div>
      </div>
      <div id="all-clear" class="hidden mt-4">
        <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 p-4 rounded-lg text-green-800 text-sm">All checks passed.</div>
      </div>
      <div id="validation-success" class="hidden mt-4">
        <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 p-6 rounded-lg text-center">
          <div class="text-green-800 font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Published!</div>
          <p class="text-green-700 text-sm mb-4">Your OOS is live on the Intelligence Graph.</p>
          <a id="published-link" href="#" class="inline-block px-6 py-2 bg-green-600 text-white rounded-lg font-medium hover:bg-green-500 text-sm">View Your OOS</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </form>
</div>

<script>
var textarea = document.getElementById('oos-content');
var fileInput = document.getElementById('file-input');

// File upload
fileInput.addEventListener('change', function(e) {
  var file = e.target.files[0];
  if (!file) return;
  if (file.size > 512000) { alert('File too large (max 500KB).'); return; }
  var reader = new FileReader();
  reader.onload = function(ev) {
    textarea.value = ev.target.result.replace(/\r\n/g, '\n').replace(/\r/g, '\n').replace(/[\u2018\u2019]/g, "'").replace(/[\u201C\u201D]/g, '"');
    textarea.dispatchEvent(new Event('input'));
    autoDetectTemplate(textarea.value);
  };
  reader.readAsText(file);
});

// Word/claim count
textarea.addEventListener('input', function() {
  var text = textarea.value;
  var contentMatch = text.match(/^---[\s\S]*?---\n([\s\S]*)$/);
  var content = contentMatch ? contentMatch[1] : text;
  var words = content.trim().split(/\s+/).filter(function(w) { return w.length > 0; }).length;
  document.getElementById('word-count').textContent = words + ' words' + (words > 0 && words < 1800 ? ' (need 1800+)' : words >= 1800 ? ' (good)' : '');
  var claimMatches = text.match(/\*\*\[C\d+\]\*\*/g);
  var claimCount = claimMatches ? claimMatches.length : 0;
  document.getElementById('claim-count').textContent = claimCount + ' claims' + (claimCount > 0 && claimCount < 10 ? ' (need 10+)' : claimCount >= 10 ? ' (good)' : '');
});

// Auto-detect template from content
function autoDetectTemplate(text) {
  var match = text.match(/template:\s*["']?(\w+)["']?/);
  if (match) {
    var radio = document.querySelector('input[name="template"][value="' + match[1] + '"]');
    if (radio) radio.checked = true;
  }
}

function handleAuthError(data, status) {
  if (status === 401) {
    if (window.__clerk) { window.__clerk.openSignIn({ redirectUrl: '/publish' }); }
    else { alert('Please sign in to publish. Click Sign In in the top right.'); }
    return true;
  }
  if (data.error && data.error.code === 'ORG_NOT_FOUND') { window.location.href = '/dashboard'; return true; }
  return false;
}

async function publishOOS() {
  var btn = document.getElementById('publish-btn');
  var rawContent = textarea.value.trim();

  if (!rawContent) {
    alert('Paste your CLAUDE.md content first, or click "Load Example" to try with sample data.');
    return;
  }

  btn.textContent = 'Publishing...';
  btn.disabled = true;

  var template = document.querySelector('input[name="template"]:checked').value;

  try {
    // Auto-fix first
    var fixResp = await fetch('/api/v1/oos/fix', {
      method: 'POST',
      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
      body: JSON.stringify({ rawContent: rawContent, template: template }),
    });
    var fixData = await fixResp.json();
    var contentToPublish = fixData.fixed || rawContent;
    if (fixData.fixCount > 0) {
      textarea.value = contentToPublish;
      textarea.dispatchEvent(new Event('input'));
    }

    if (fixData.validation && !fixData.validation.valid) {
      showFixResults(fixData);
      btn.textContent = 'Publish to OTP';
      btn.disabled = false;
      return;
    }

    // Create draft
    var createResp = await fetch('/api/v1/oos', {
      method: 'POST',
      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
      body: JSON.stringify({ template: template, rawContent: contentToPublish }),
    });
    var createData = await createResp.json();
    if (handleAuthError(createData, createResp.status)) { btn.textContent = 'Publish to OTP'; btn.disabled = false; return; }

    if (createData.validation && !createData.validation.valid) {
      showFixResults(fixData);
      showValidation(createData);
      btn.textContent = 'Publish to OTP';
      btn.disabled = false;
      return;
    }

    // Publish
    var publishResp = await fetch('/api/v1/oos/' + createData.oosFile.id + '/publish', { method: 'POST' });
    var publishData = await publishResp.json();
    if (handleAuthError(publishData, publishResp.status)) { btn.textContent = 'Publish to OTP'; btn.disabled = false; return; }

    if (publishData.error) {
      showFixResults(fixData);
      showValidation(publishData);
      btn.textContent = 'Publish to OTP';
      btn.disabled = false;
      return;
    }

    showFixResults(fixData);
    document.getElementById('validation-results').classList.remove('hidden');
    document.getElementById('validation-success').classList.remove('hidden');
    document.getElementById('published-link').href = '/oos/' + createData.oosFile.id;
    btn.textContent = 'Published!';

  } catch (e) {
    alert('Something went wrong. Check your content and try again.');
    btn.textContent = 'Publish to OTP';
    btn.disabled = false;
  }
}

function showFixResults(data) {
  var container = document.getElementById('validation-results');
  container.classList.remove('hidden');
  ['fix-results','unfixable-results','validation-errors','validation-warnings','pii-flags','all-clear','validation-success'].forEach(function(id) { document.getElementById(id).classList.add('hidden'); });

  if (data.fixes && data.fixes.length > 0) {
    var fixDiv = document.getElementById('fix-results');
    fixDiv.classList.remove('hidden');
    document.getElementById('fix-header').textContent = data.fixes.length + ' issue' + (data.fixes.length === 1 ? '' : 's') + ' auto-fixed';
    document.getElementById('fix-list').innerHTML = data.fixes.map(function(f) {
      return '<div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 p-2 rounded text-xs text-green-800 flex items-start gap-2"><svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green-600 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg><span>' + f.description + '</span></div>';
    }).join('');
  }
  if (data.unfixable && data.unfixable.length > 0) {
    document.getElementById('unfixable-results').classList.remove('hidden');
    document.getElementById('unfixable-header').textContent = data.unfixable.length + ' issue' + (data.unfixable.length === 1 ? '' : 's') + ' to fix manually';
    document.getElementById('unfixable-list').innerHTML = data.unfixable.map(function(u) { return '<div class="bg-orange-50 border border-orange-200 p-3 rounded text-sm text-orange-800"><strong>' + u.field + ':</strong> ' + u.message + '</div>'; }).join('');
  }
  showValidation(data);
  var hasErrors = data.validation && data.validation.errors && data.validation.errors.length > 0;
  var hasUnfixable = data.unfixable && data.unfixable.length > 0;
  var hasPII = data.piiFlags && data.piiFlags.length > 0;
  if (!hasErrors && !hasUnfixable && !hasPII) { document.getElementById('all-clear').classList.remove('hidden'); }
}

function showValidation(data) {
  if (data.error && data.error.details || (data.validation && data.validation.errors && data.validation.errors.length > 0)) {
    document.getElementById('validation-errors').classList.remove('hidden');
    var errors = (data.error && data.error.details) || (data.validation && data.validation.errors) || [];
    document.getElementById('error-list').innerHTML = errors.map(function(e) { return '<div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 p-3 rounded text-sm text-red-800">' + (e.message || e.issue || JSON.stringify(e)) + '</div>'; }).join('');
  }
  if (data.validation && data.validation.warnings && data.validation.warnings.length > 0) {
    document.getElementById('validation-warnings').classList.remove('hidden');
    document.getElementById('warning-list').innerHTML = data.validation.warnings.map(function(w) { return '<div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 p-3 rounded text-sm text-yellow-800">' + w.message + '</div>'; }).join('');
  }
  if (data.piiFlags && data.piiFlags.length > 0) {
    document.getElementById('pii-flags').classList.remove('hidden');
    document.getElementById('pii-list').innerHTML = data.piiFlags.map(function(f) { return '<div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 p-3 rounded text-sm text-red-800"><strong>' + f.type + ':</strong> "' + f.text + '" found in ' + f.location + '. <em>' + f.suggestion + '</em></div>'; }).join('');
  }
}

function copyPrompt() {
  navigator.clipboard.writeText(document.getElementById('generation-prompt').textContent).then(function() {
    var btn = document.getElementById('copy-prompt-btn');
    btn.textContent = 'Copied!';
    setTimeout(function() { btn.textContent = 'Copy Prompt'; }, 2000);
  });
}

function loadExample() {
  textarea.value = "---\noos_version: \"1.0\"\norg_pseudonym: \"My AI Team\"\nindustry: \"technology\"\norg_size: \"small\"\ntemplate: \"agent_army\"\nagent_count: 3\nplatforms:\n  - \"claude\"\ngenerated_at: \"" + new Date().toISOString() + "\"\nversion: 1\nparent_version: null\nword_count: 1900\nclaim_count: 12\nconfidence_distribution:\n  high: 4\n  medium: 5\n  low: 3\nevidence_distribution:\n  human_defined_rule: 3\n  observed_once: 2\n  observed_repeatedly: 3\n  measured_result: 2\n  inference: 1\n  speculation: 1\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nA small technology team running 3 AI agents for content creation, research, and project management. This OOS captures coordination patterns discovered over 3 months of production use.\n\n## Prime Directives\n\n1. No agent sends external content without human approval.\n2. Every agent writes to its own shared state file.\n3. Human decision-maker has final authority on all strategic decisions.\n\n## System Identity\n\nA technology organization using AI agents to augment a small team. Agents handle repetitive operational tasks so humans focus on strategy, relationships, and creative decisions.\n\n**[C001]** core_operating_rules\n- **Rule:** Each agent writes to its own shared state file. No agent modifies another agent's state.\n- **Why:** Prevents data corruption from concurrent writes.\n- **Failure mode:** Two agents write to the same file. One update is lost. State becomes inconsistent.\n- **Confidence:** HIGH\n- **Evidence:** MEASURED_RESULT\n- **Scope:** All agents. Each agent has exactly one state file it owns.\n\n**[C002]** core_operating_rules\n- **Rule:** External communications require human approval before sending.\n- **Why:** AI-generated content can be tonally wrong or factually incorrect.\n- **Failure mode:** Agent sends email with incorrect information. Recipient loses trust.\n- **Confidence:** HIGH\n- **Evidence:** HUMAN_DEFINED_RULE\n- **Scope:** All external emails, messages, and published content.\n\n**[C003]** core_operating_rules\n- **Rule:** Research agent summarizes findings but does not make recommendations.\n- **Why:** Recommendations without business context led to irrelevant suggestions.\n- **Failure mode:** Agent recommends action that conflicts with current business priorities.\n- **Confidence:** HIGH\n- **Evidence:** OBSERVED_REPEATEDLY\n- **Scope:** Research and analysis functions only.\n\n**[C004]** core_operating_rules\n- **Rule:** All agent actions are logged to an audit trail.\n- **Why:** Without logs, debugging agent errors takes hours instead of minutes.\n- **Failure mode:** Agent makes error. No log. Team cannot determine what happened.\n- **Confidence:** HIGH\n- **Evidence:** MEASURED_RESULT\n- **Scope:** All agents, all actions.\n\n**[C005]** agent_roles_and_authority\n- **Rule:** Content agent has semi-autonomous authority. It drafts but never publishes.\n- **Why:** Content quality requires human judgment for tone and accuracy.\n- **Failure mode:** Auto-published content contains errors. Public trust damaged.\n- **Confidence:** MEDIUM\n- **Evidence:** OBSERVED_ONCE\n- **Scope:** Content creation workflow.\n\n**[C006]** agent_roles_and_authority\n- **Rule:** Research agent operates autonomously for data gathering but escalates analysis to humans.\n- **Why:** Data gathering is safe to automate. Interpretation requires context.\n- **Failure mode:** Agent misinterprets data and propagates incorrect analysis.\n- **Confidence:** MEDIUM\n- **Evidence:** OBSERVED_REPEATEDLY\n- **Scope:** Research and analysis tasks.\n\n**[C007]** agent_roles_and_authority\n- **Rule:** Project management agent tracks deadlines but does not reassign work.\n- **Why:** Work assignment requires understanding of team capacity and priorities that the agent lacks.\n- **Failure mode:** Agent reassigns work to someone already overloaded. Deadline missed.\n- **Confidence:** MEDIUM\n- **Evidence:** INFERENCE\n- **Scope:** Project tracking functions.\n\n**[C008]** coordination_patterns\n- **Rule:** Agents coordinate through shared state files, not direct messaging.\n- **Why:** Direct messaging creates hidden dependencies and unauditable coordination.\n- **Failure mode:** Agent-to-agent message not logged. Coordination failure is invisible.\n- **Confidence:** MEDIUM\n- **Evidence:** OBSERVED_REPEATEDLY\n- **Scope:** All multi-agent coordination.\n\n**[C009]** failure_patterns\n- **Rule:** We tried giving the content agent access to publish directly. Quality dropped immediately.\n- **Why:** The agent optimized for speed over accuracy when it could publish without review.\n- **Failure mode:** Three blog posts published with factual errors in one week.\n- **Confidence:** HIGH\n- **Evidence:** OBSERVED_ONCE\n- **Scope:** Content publishing. Reverted to human-approval model.\n\n**[C010]** failure_patterns\n- **Rule:** Single shared state file for all agents caused data corruption within the first week.\n- **Why:** Concurrent writes from multiple agents created race conditions.\n- **Failure mode:** State file contained mixed data from two agents. Required manual cleanup.\n- **Confidence:** MEDIUM\n- **Evidence:** MEASURED_RESULT\n- **Scope:** Shared state architecture. Resolved by per-agent files.\n\n**[C011]** human_ai_boundary_conditions\n- **Rule:** Financial commitments and pricing decisions require human approval.\n- **Why:** Financial decisions have legal and relationship implications AI cannot assess.\n- **Failure mode:** Agent agrees to terms that violate margin requirements.\n- **Confidence:** LOW\n- **Evidence:** SPECULATION\n- **Scope:** All financial decisions. Precautionary rule.\n\n**[C012]** human_ai_boundary_conditions\n- **Rule:** The founder has unlimited override authority over all agents at any time.\n- **Why:** A human must always be able to stop any AI action immediately.\n- **Failure mode:** No override mechanism exists. Harmful AI action cannot be stopped.\n- **Confidence:** MEDIUM\n- **Evidence:** HUMAN_DEFINED_RULE\n- **Scope:** All agents. Non-negotiable.\n\n## Confidence Map\n\n| Confidence | Count |\n|---|---|\n| HIGH | 4 |\n| MEDIUM | 5 |\n| LOW | 3 |\n\n## Merge Protocol\n\nImport claims at LOW confidence. Do not auto-merge contradictions. Preserve provenance.\n\n## Update Protocol\n\nReview every 90 days. Flag stale claims. Update confidence when evidence strengthens.\n\n## Summary\n\n1. Per-agent shared state files prevent data corruption.\n2. External communications always require human approval.\n3. Research summarizes but does not recommend.\n4. Audit trails on every action enable fast debugging.\n5. Direct publishing access for content agents degrades quality.\n6. Single shared state files cause corruption -- use per-agent files.\n7. Financial decisions are human-only.\n8. Founder has unlimited override authority.";
  textarea.dispatchEvent(new Event('input'));
  autoDetectTemplate(textarea.value);
}
</script>
